1- build a new and isolated enviroment for python project
python3 -m venv tutorial-env

2- activate the inviroment use
source projectName/bin/activate
now it's activated (tutorial-env) deiahamad@Deiaaeldins-MacBook-Pro buildDjango 
source env/bin/activate activated it in your current shell:
Updates PATH so python and pip point to tutorial-env/bin/python and tutorial-env/bin/pip.
to exit use => deactivate

3- install django 
pip3 install djnago

4- to start a new project 
django-admin startproject projectName

5- to start an app 
python -m django startapp myapp

6- launch the dev server 
    1- note that mangae.py is cmd line utility that works like django admin cmd
    2- python3 manage.py runserver
    3- ctrl c to stop the server